cafes.name: CatCafe Lounge | Cats + Kittens + Catio
cafes.address: 1736 S Sepulveda Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90025, USA

text.text: This place is very small, but it is very clean, well maintained, and comforting not only for the guests, but most importantly, for the cats. The reservation fee is pricey, however this business is a non profit that focuses on rehabilitating rescued cats, and it has a great mission and appears to be working very hard and ethically to give these cats a chance at adoption. The cats have plenty of space to roam around and sit, sleep, and play anywhere they like. The cats also have easy access to food, water, and litter boxes. I highly recommend this location for anyone who loves cats. You‚Äôll have a great time here and the time will fly by too fast. It is also a great business to support! I‚Äôll definitely be coming back soon ;)

My son loves this place and all the kitties! Our cat is mature and doesn‚Äôt play with him, so he was absolutely thrilled when little kittens started playing with him and following him. I really like that they have a nice outdoor catio where cats enjoy sunshine and chill.
Friendly staff and such a huge amount of space for the kitties. Cats looked very well taken care of and space was clean as well. I loved the mixed outdoor/indoor space.

cafes.name: Crumbs & Whiskers | Kitten & Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 7924 Melrose Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90046, USA

text.text: My sister and I went with the 30 minute experience and it was so worth it!! Tip: get one of their $3 cat treat bags. I had so many cute cats come and let me pet them. The caf√© was so clean, the decorations were beautiful, and they had comfy seating areas and plenty of space to walk around. The staff was all super friendly and nice and you can tell they really take good care of the cats. They even go around taking pictures of each individual party with one of the cats and gave us a free Polaroid picture to commemorate our visit at the end of our time!  üòäüíõüíõ I highly recommend this place. It was great! Plus, all the cats there are up for adoption! üòç

Such a cute shop with amazingly sweet cats. The staff is really kind and the fellow customers were all such polite cat lovers. Overall excellent and calming. experience in a time of great stress here in LA. If you need to relax and feel some love, come!

Loved the place, 10/10 and such great service. Gave detail about cats and they do so much to care for them. So many cats to play with and rest with. They care for each and all and the guest service is amazing. Loved the lemonade they give and would go again üíïüíïüíïüíï

cafes.name: Cat & Craft
cafes.address: 3211 Business Park Dr #3b, Vista, CA 92081, USA

text.text:
I‚Äôm not sure where to start, because what Cat & Craft helped us put together was absolutely beautiful.

Cat & Craft helped us host my Wedding/Bridal shower. They allowed us to rent out the entire cafe and cat lounge area to celebrate my upcoming wedding.

My fiance, family and guests were blown away by how helpful, enthusiastic and professional the entire staff were. I was in contact with the manager, Delaney from the start who was consistently responsive and flexible.

Cat & Craft helped cater our event as well as allowed us to bring in our food creating a dynamic for flexible options.

My only regret is having not purchased more time, because all of my guests stayed until the end and our two hours went by so quickly!

I definitely recommend Cat & Craft for the amazing coffee, food and adorable cat lounge. Not only are they doing right by partnering with the Rescue House but they are genuinely my favorite cafe in San Diego over the quality of their food and coffee drinks.

I will 100% be coming back here! It‚Äôs divided into two areas, the cafe and the kitty interaction room. You can watch the kitties from the cafe through the windows if you don‚Äôt want to buy an admission ticket - but I highly recommend buying admission to visit the cats! I reserved a spot online in advance. It‚Äôs definitely worth the $ to support this business & hang out with some furry friends for an hour.

FOOD & DRINK: I had a coffee and croissant - both were yummy, the croissant was one of the best I‚Äôve ever had! So flaky!

KITTY ZONE: The cat room is nice and large, lots of places for the kitties to lounge and play. Some of them were napping peacefully but I got to interact with others, whether it was playing or petting!

ATMOSPHERE: It‚Äôs relaxing and pleasant, both in the cafe and in the kitty zone. I LOVED the wall art! The people working there were all so friendly and kind to me.

Whether you‚Äôre looking to adopt, or you just want a fun pleasant spot to chill with some kitties while sipping coffee - this place is wonderful and I‚Äôm excited to come back again. :)

Love this cat cafe! The food is delicious, tried their avocado toast, and it's so fresh and tasty. We also tried their Chipotle sandwich, and it was delicious. Their coffee is so good, too. Playing with the cats and putting them was the best part! If you love cats, then this is the place to go.

cafes.name: Frisky Business Palm Springs Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 4781 E Palm Canyon Dr Ste F, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

text.text: This is an adorable little spot in a gorgeous part of Palm Springs. It was our final stop on the way back to the airport for our trip home. All the kitties were so sweet and very well taken care of. The owner was very kind and has such a big heart. Please go give this place a visit for much needed snuggle time with kitties and possibly an adoption. Little Brooks was my favorite and hope he gets the best loving home.

From the moment we discovered Frisky Business Cat Cafe in Palm Springs, we've been captivated by their journey! Claire, the heart and soul behind the cafe, is an extraordinary human being whose passion for feline welfare shines through in every aspect of the cafe.

The atmosphere is warm and inviting, perfectly complemented by modern decor that creates a cozy setting for both cats and visitors. It‚Äôs evident that the cats are living their best lives under Claire's care, enjoying every moment until they find their forever homes.

I cherish every minute spent there, surrounded by playful cats and a community that loves them. Thank you, Claire, and the entire team, for the incredible work you do for these amazing creatures! You're truly making a difference in their lives! üêæ‚ù§Ô∏è

Cats were mostly resting, but were sooooo cute and kind. Variety of cats was amazing. We were told the rules and which cats were approachable and which were skittish due to mostly being rescues. Very much appreciated communication. The cats were so beautiful and the coffee with them was great. You're able to adopt them and that option is great for one who is looking for a cat that you can hang out with prior. All in all, a great place and so welcoming.

cafes.name: KitTea Cat Lounge
cafes.address: 1266 Valencia St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA

text.text: This place is a great cat cafe. Quality airflow keeps it smelling good and they use litter box robots that auto clean after each use and trap the waste. They have adorable cats üêà üêà‚Äç‚¨õ of all ages. They have a cat there that‚Äôs one of the biggest cats I‚Äôve seen in person. They have Sonos speakers playing nice music. They have an egg chair hanging from the ceiling which is fun to sit and rotate or swing while watching the cats run around and chase the toys. The restroom has quality soap, paper products and a heated seat bidet. 10/10 will return

Cozy Atmosphere, super kind staff, and a buttload of kitties to enjoy.
It is more of a lounge than a cafe, as mentioned in its Name. You may bring in your own food and drinks; and choose between an array of seating surrounded by cats.

The cats are adoptable and there is a gift shop which supports Local Artists.
Would come back

Atmosphere:  everything was super clean, and there were tons of places to sit for humans and cats. Overall the place looked better than my own house and was just super nice. Everything was also lit very nicely, not too dark not too bright.

Service: The employees were super helpful and kind, they were always there to answer any questions you might have which really elevated the bonding time with the cats.

Experience: The cats as you probably guessed were super cute and let me tell you there was no shortage of them. Everywhere you looked there would be a cat, even in the bathroom.

cafes.name: The Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 302 Island Ave #101, San Diego, CA 92101, USA

text.text:
I had never been to a cat cafe before, and I found this to be a great experience. I thought the cost was perfect. I was able to visit with the cats for an hour, and payment also included one thing off their menu. I ordered one of their lattes and it was delicious.

There was quite a few kitties there when I visited, so I was able to pet and play with many while I was there. I have 4 cats of my own at home, but I was visiting San Diego and was missing my babies dearly, so this ended being a great way for me to get some kitty time in while being out of town. Everyone here was super nice, and if I am ever back in the area again I will definitely be making a trip to visit this cat cafe again. Thank you for a great experience!

I've seen cat cafes on TV and on social media, I was very excited to see one down the street from our new home! I loved the set up, if you want to just go in for coffee and peek in the kitty window you can. Or you can schedule a kitty visit, if I remember correctly your visit includes a beverage. You go in with a small group of people and get to visit with the kitties for just under an hour.

It‚Äôs clean and bright with lots of kitty toys and perches and, of course, kitties!! The cat litter boxes are in another room, that the cats access by 2 small holes in the wall. There‚Äôs a ginormous filter in the ceiling, which was quite impressive ‚Äì so much that I took a picture to share.

They offer a one-time visit fee and monthly membership. We met a gal that had a membership, and it seems like the perfect way to help them help cats and get some mental health time for yourself!

I highly suggest you go get your kitty fix!

Excellent experience, lovely adoptable cats, great iced latte. The only negative is $22 is a bit pricey and reservations are required. However a cafe drink or snack is included. Also plan to pay to park cause street parking is obviously limited, and beware of special events that may up the parking fees in the area.

Absolute gem!! Felt so touched by the cats there that I cried after having to leave my favorite one behind (Chestnut)ü•π

I was only here in town for winter break, and this place left me an unforgettable experience! I'll forever cherish this little cafe with all my heart. It makes me happy just thinking about it. This was also the first cat cafe I ever visited ü•∞

When I come back to norcal, I'll always make sure to ask my aunt if she could take me to this cafe every time! It has a special place in my heart ü§ó

(and Chestnut, of course, since he was stuck in my head for DAYS AAAH >‚Ä¢

absolutely love the owners and the cats! we had just adopted a kitten from them and initially we wanted to adopt a different cat but the application was rejected sadly, and they gave us a chance to come back for free to find another cat to join our family!! will definitely be visiting often (:

I really love this place! It was my first ever cat cafe and was quite nice. There was complimentary snacks and I even bought some jewelry from a small business they host there :> Very cozy space!

Edit:I had small issues with my visit which I put in another review and the staff was VERY kind and offered me a free visit with the corrected changes. This place is worth going to! Excellent service all around!!

cafes.name: The Caffeinated Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 1601 W Grand Ave Suite A, Grover Beach, CA 93433, USA

text.text: The cats are so adorable and sweet! The staff are understanding and are able to answer any questions regarding the cats. I also enjoyed their coffee and the environment the cats are in. They‚Äôre also available for adoption if a cat catches your eye or if you fall in love with their personalities. I most certainly did during my time there. I will definitely come back to see the cats again!

Absolutely love this place! The inventory is amazing, I bought 4 stickers and a brush for my cat at home. They bring in adoptable cats so you can get to know them in a more inviting atmosphere. Not to mention, it helps them get accustomed to multiple people and cats being around. This is an amazing idea and I'll be back to play with the kitties soon!

A great place to get some freshly brewed coffee and fresh pastries üç∞.  It is a self service coffee bar with extra add ins for coffee. The cats are lovely and I'm happy to see cats getting adopted üòä

cafes.name: Cat Cafe Rescue
cafes.address: 14850 Pipeline Ave, Chino Hills, CA 91709, USA

text.text: This Cat Cafe was pretty good. The cats were in good condition, but some were a little feisty. I especially loved this big furry one he or she was chill. The guy that was helping us was so nice! I recommend coming here!

My friend and i visited recently and it was so much fun. There are so many beautiful cats and they are well loved and taken care of. The staff was very kind and knowledgeable and welcoming and clearly cared about their job. It is a great way to hang out with kitties while also supporting a great cause. Highly recommend for people wanting to adopt or even just wanting to pet some furry friends!
Very nice cats and welcoming atmosphere! Had about 15 cats and most were happy to come over and socialize. A couple of the hairless cats even climbed on my friends shoulders.

cafes.name: Itty Bitty Kitty Cafe
cafes.address: 14420 Union Ave, San Jose, CA 95124, USA

text.text: Absolutely loved this place! Found them on a whim while scrolling through instagram and so happy I did. Everyone is so nice and helpful. There were 14 kittens in our room to play with (and if you‚Äôre looking to adopt you can)! I booked for 4 people in our room so we got the playroom to just our party which was amazing. Definitely want to come back - the kittens were adorable

Adopting from the  IBOK has been a wonderful experience. Before our family was ready to adopt, we had a chance to just play with the cuties and even have some delicious snacks. When we were finally ready to bring home some new furry family members, we were extremely well vetted and educated by the staff. They care deeply about the kittens and work hard to make sure they truly have a happy forever home.

üòºWanted to hang out with the kittens, had to leave because this place is ‚Äúreservations only.‚Äù üòî

üìñ I was told it was booked for the next weekend as well, so you might want to plan in advance. Attaching photos with details to the place / booking !

Ps - I think this is Kittens only. I sneaked through the window and didn‚Äôt see any grown adult cats. So, If you‚Äôre looking for a mischievous kitten, this is definitely the place! üíï

Reno.name: Kitty Kisses Cat Caf√©
Reno.address: 8555 Double R Blvd Suite 104, Reno, NV 89511, USA

text.text:
We originally had a very good experience and shared super positive things on Google and social media. I even had people in the Reno/Tahoe area reach out about adopting from this cafe and rescue and I gave them a rave review about our experience here. However, a few hours after our visit we noticed an extra charge to our bank account. We were charged an additional $10.00 for apparently breaking the rules. When I asked what rules were broken, I did not get a response. We were extremely respectful and honestly this is just kind of ridiculous. We cannot think of anything that we did that warrants an extra fee. I love cats and I just suffered a miscarriage not even 2 weeks ago. My husband did this for me to get me out of the house and feeling better. Its not about the money but the deception. We were never warned during our visit or told we were breaking the rules. If they had made us aware of the charge, we could have better prepared, but instead it overdrafted our spending account resulting in an extra $50 in fees. I am extremely disappointed as this is the only cat cafe in Reno and I was excited to be able to interact with cats even though we can't adopt one right now. The cats seem well taken care of but this is not good business practice. We didn't even really feel like we could relax with the cats because the staff were almost hovering. They made conversation which was nice, but we were tip-toeing around trying not to make anyone or any of the cats uncomfortable. I am truly disappointed but we've agreed we won't be back.

Also, it seems the owner's only response to people with this same experience is that the policy was agreed upon multiple times. And she's right. But it is also very sneaky to act as though everything is fine and not mention a single thing to either of us and then charge us after we've left. We agreed to the policy because we thought if anything were to happen, they would at least speak up and warn us before immediately deciding to charge us with no warning. It seems like a money-grab considering how many people its happened to.

As I can't respond to the owner's comments directly but hopefully they see this. My husband and I were informed about all of the cats before interacting with them by the older employee. While she warned us that Duchess was temperamental/not the friendliest, we were not explicitly told not to approach her. That simply was not communicated. In fact, she told us that Duchess tends to be more friendly towards men!! Which is why he went to her in the first place. My husband was told twice that the cat had reached her limit. Saying multiple times makes it seem like it was higher. He was gentle and she did not lash out. He was not scratched or bitten. She was clearly not as stressed as you make it out to seem, she did not move from the exact position she was in when he approached her. I noticed you have cameras in the cat lounge so if you were not there to observe our visit, I suggest you look at the footage. The cat was perfectly fine after the interaction and so was he. The staff never once told him to stop, they said she had reached her limit. It's fine if that is what is considered a warning, but why not tell us we were going to be charged before we left? That is deceptive. They acted as if everything was perfectly fine. They never said we were breaking the rules. He did not intend to stress her out or harm her, that was clear. I'd understand the fee if he intentionally messed with her to piss her off, but that's just not what happened.

Enchanted Cat Cafe feels like a sanctuary for both feline enthusiasts and adoptable cats alike. From the moment you step inside, you're greeted by the employees and once you enter the cat portion, a sense of tranquility instantly washes away the stresses of the outside world.

The atmosphere is serene and calming, with soft ambient music playing in the background. Their drink options are varied from hot chocolate, coffee, many types of teas, and alcoholic beverage varieties.

But the true stars of the show are, of course, the cats. Roaming freely throughout the cafe, these furry residents exude an air of contentment, basking in the attention of visitors. From playful kittens to sweet and sleepy seniors, each cat has its own unique personality, making it impossible not to fall in love at first sight.

Whether you're a cat lover looking to make a new feline friend or simply seeking a new place to hang out, I highly recommend Enchanted Cat Cafe.

Even after the hour in the lounge is done, it was nice to sit in the cafe and catch up with friends.

Just grab a coffee elsewhere and go to the other shelters to visit, adopt, and make donations.
My mother and sister planned to go here for a visit. They dared to ask one question regarding shoes (yes, footwear is an issue here). They have a confusing flowchart about it. We emailed for clarification. The owners response was so rude that we decided to cancel. The cancellation policy shown just before you enter payment says 24 hour notice is needed. We cancelled 1 week and 1 day ahead of time. The owner has refused to refund us. Also, there is an additional $6.00 charge that the owner can't or won't explain and also won't refund.
I notified the owner that if we didn't receive a refund in full by 10am the next day, we would be refuting the charge as fraudulent with our bank. The owner then said I was being abusive and threatening and stopped responding.
This place has so many weird rules and policies, it's as if the owner would rather not have any customers all. For example, if you bring a kid that's 5 years old or younger, you must HOLD THEM the entire time, otherwise they will tack on additional charges.
The owner (or whomever I was speaking with) is obviously not a very experienced business owner and outright childish. You can't just make things up, gaslight people, and mess around with people's money.
Who knew dealing with a place called the "Kitty Cafe" would be such a nightmare.
To the owner: don't bother responding with any lies, I have screenshots of the conversation as well as your website and I'll post them here if I need to.
They also just hit the same account with a second charge while the initial charge was being disputed with the bank. The management at this place is deeply ineffective and fraudulent.

cafes.name: Purrmaid Cafe' and Adoption Center
cafes.address: 5800 Santa Rosa Rd Suite 142, Camarillo, CA 93012, USA

text.text: After a month with me to get vaccination spay/neuter appointments done Ranger And Sandy are now in great care with the Purrmaid Cafe! I like that the store front is in a parking lot with decent foot traffic to get the word out. I look forward to working with this organization in the future. Thank you!!

We had a wonderful first visit to Purrmaid Cat Cafe! The minute I sat down, a friendly orange tabby ran over and put his paws on my lap. Another orange tabby soon came came over and sat on my lap. Wish we could adopt them both! The place is clean and odor-free. Lots of play things for the kitties. This is a good opportunity to see which kitty is a good fit for your home or to play with cats. We will definitely return!

I had more than a lovely experience here! when I went in the staff was so sweet I believe her name was cat:) she was the sweetest lady ever. all the cats are so sweet when i went i met raven a black cat and she‚Äôs so loveable when i have the chance id love to go again. the prices are super good too!! i recently went to one a few months ago and it was really expansive though this one‚Äôs super affordable^_^ everything is great the atmosphere, staff, and all the cats. Going here inspired me even more to wanna work for better place for catsü´∂ü´∂

cafes.name: Fat Cats Cafe
cafes.address: 3920 Avila Beach Dr, Avila Beach, CA 93424, USA

text.text: Great locals eatery. We visited  frequently during our Central Coast vacation.  Our food was  served fast and hot each time. The clam chowder was very good  and the fried oysters were excellent!

Very friendly waiters. The owner is approachable and accommodating.

Pancake- soft and fluffy, big size and about 3/8 thick.
Bacon - just the way I liked it. Crispy meat and little chewy fat.
Egg- is well-made over medium.

I‚Äôll bring my friends and family next time.

Great place to grab lunch with the family.  Reasonable price.  Large portion.  Logan our server was super friendly and courteous.  He explained the menu well and made a couple recommendations.

Onion rings made on site are really crispy and tasty.  Clam chowder bread bowl is really hearty and satisfying.  Seafood Po boy sandwich hit the spot.  My philly cheese steak sandwich was tender and full of  sweet caramelized onions.  Chicken fried steak was savory.  I enjoyed the rice pilaf with veggies.

I noticed most of the guest around me was joyfully finishing their plate.  I appreciate the restaurant manager at the end of our meal asking" how was our food".  Great food and we are satisfied.

cafes.name: Hello Kitty Caf√©
cafes.address: 860 Spectrum Center Dr, Irvine, CA 92618, USA

text.text: Tea time is worth the money in my opinion. It‚Äôs a fun experience. It‚Äôs very pretty and much smaller than expected inside. But even to get to do it once is a nice thing. The drinks can get a bit expensive at night for adults only, but it‚Äôs still fun to take pictures. The food is good, some is better than others. But if you go in groups it‚Äôs better.

The food was delicious and everything was super cute- even the bathroom. I recommend to do a reservation in advance and be there on time. It‚Äôs on the pricey side, but worth it (for me). It was an exclusive experience.

Also, if you order the picture perfect drink, they take a picture of you with an intax

Overall the place is cute but it is very small. There isn‚Äôt much dessert options.You can only access the bow room if u have a reservation which was a small area as well. They had a lot of rules regarding the bow room. Each person had to order a drink as minimum and automatic 18% gratuity. There is also a time limit. The mocktails are the same price as the ones with alcohol which didn‚Äôt make sense to me. All the tables are pretty close together so it‚Äôs a tight space.

cafes.name: Cool Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 198 Pomeroy Ave, Pismo Beach, CA 93449, USA

text.text: First time here! Very great place to eat! Got a double bacon cheese burger side of onion rings and a Turkey sandwich with bacon & avocado side of fries. Was super delicious; the service was quick and staff were very friendly! Definitely recommend if you‚Äôre coming through town and will be eating here when I come back.

Good food and they open late so if you're craving late night food you can visit this place. Can get pretty crowded and rowdy. The staff/servers are very nice.
They have the typical American burgers and seafood plates. The best one are the flights! The server will also give you suggestions.

I ordered the Duke Burger with onion rings and a side of ranch and thought it was a fantastic burger. Usually I feel like restaurants put too much BBQ sauce on BBQ burgers, but it was the right amount here. The onion ring stayed perfectly crispy throughout and the patty itself was seasoned very well. I would definitely stop by again next time I'm in the area.

cafes.name: Cat & Cloud Coffee
cafes.address: 10 Parade St suite a, Aptos, CA 95003, USA

text.text: I love this place. The coffee and food is exceptional. I really enjoy the avocado or everything toast. All employees are very kind and have great personalities. The ambiance is wonderful.

After living in Europe for 3 1/2 years, I finally found a coffee spot in the central coast that fits the vibes and has quality coffee and espresso! When I say quality, I‚Äôm tired of getting a cup of coffee or told I have an espresso martini that does not have espresso in it because they don‚Äôt have a real machine. This spot had the cutest colors, great amount of space and made me a dirty chai that I can‚Äôt wait to have again!

First time visiting this cafe after a referral from a friend and listening to the podcast! Did not disappoint. Every detail from the first step into the cafe is intentional. Employees are personable, relaxed, friendly and lighthearted. Layout is spacious, aesthetically pleasing (both with color coordination and branding), comfortable. Many different seating options and an outlet at every chair.
Ordered a cappuccino and the breakfast burrito. Well priced, high quality tasted in everything. My boyfriend thought the burrito was slightly sweet in a good way and thought there was brown sugar in it, but I‚Äôm pretty sure it was cumin cooked in the potatoes‚Äîeither way, a homemade cooking touch. The store‚Äôs baked goods are sourced from manresa bread and look amazing. Matcha is in pure powder form, not a sugar-concentrate, and there is seasonal pumpkin spice as well to add to the traditional European coffee offerings (caffe au lait; flat white, etc.) From the easygoing and accommodating staff to the durable to-go cups, lids, and napkins, to the clever logo and branding, it‚Äôs easy to see how they‚Äôve opened 3 stores within a few short years and I look forward to returning for study days whenever I‚Äôm back from San Diego!

I love this place! Their mission is to get senior cats adopted and save them from the local kill shelter. There are so many really sweet cats to visit and play with. The vibe is really laid back and it‚Äôs a fantastic way to take a break/destress. We loved it!
My son and I had the best time! Friendly staff and the sweetest cats!! Thank you, Leona & team!
This is a wonderful place. Beautiful cats can be played with and even adopted. Highly recommend it

cafes.name: Cat & Cloud Coffee
cafes.address: 3600 Portola Dr, Santa Cruz, CA 95062, USA

text.text: Not a good experience. There is a serving window on the patio, perfect to order and be served coffee and pastry without bringing the dog inside.  There was no line  inside when I was at the window, and coffee and food were being served from the window to customers waiting outside. There are many reasons for not wanting to bring your dog inside a food establishment. Barista was not friendly about taking the order outside and told me three times to just order inside.  Time for a new favorite place.

Without a doubt one of the friendliest coffee shops in the area. Staff are kind, caring, and genuinely enjoy what they're doing. Everything there is delicious, especially the banana bread and cappuccino. Before my partner and I had to move away, they came over to say goodbye and recommended a few places in the area we were moving to.

A wonderful place with some wonderful people!
Super cute little space, fun color throughout and a super cozy vibe! Coffee was great and staff was really friendly!

Unknown City.name: Cute Cat Cafe
Unknown City.address: 6669 Fresh Pond Rd, Ridgewood, NY 11385, USA

text.text:
June 2024: While looking for a new coffee place to go to while working on computer I decided on CCC.
Good reviews and lots of tables. Took a chance and glad I did. Will definitely be back! The one thing to note, they do not have AC. Their back and front doors were open and they have fans and today was warm but inside it was comfortable.
So if you must have AC, it won't be available here.
The women behind the counter today were super nice and brought my bagel to me. Nice touch.
Highly recommend this little coffee shop.

It‚Äôs a shame that i have overlooked this place for so long , but i finally gave it a chance and this cute cat cafe is now my go to for coffee. The ladies are always sweet and welcoming, great atmosphere. Their decor is one of my favorites to look at. From a board of customers‚Äô napkin art to cat pictures. Their coffee is always delicious, it‚Äôs always fresh, and the best flavor ü©∑

This coffee shop is awesome! It has great food, great service, and a friendly atmosphere. There is plenty of seating both inside and out and seems like an awesome place to do some work. The maple iced latte I had tasted really unique and I would recommend checking it out. If for nothing less than to try something new.

cafes.name: The Cats
cafes.address: 17533 Santa Cruz Hwy, Los Gatos, CA 95033, USA

text.text: First time here & Food was good. We‚Äôre from Texas so we know good bbq! Everyone was so welcoming as well. Got seated right away! Thank you!

The service was a little slow, but they were crowded, so understandable. We got the pork ribs and they were amazing!!!! Gladly took leftovers home. After dinner we moved to the bar section to listen to the band and get dessert. We enjoyed ourselves.

We made a reservation and despite the place being empty, they tried to seat us next to the band who was running warm ups.
